hreia elaboration and the complete argument to display Jesus’ identity as the Light of the World. This analysis illustrates the inseparability of form and content, rhetoric and theology, in the Fourth Gospel.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 4aAntike Rhetorik. 4aAuslegungsgeschichte. 4aJohannesevangelium. 4aProgymnasmata. 4aZwei-Ebenen-Drama. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / New Testament.2bisacsh  aAncient Rhetoric.  aGospel of John.  aHistory of Interpretation.  aProgymnasmata.  aTwo-Level Drama.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2009z978311021952408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWISS./JUDAISTIK  2009z9783110219494oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311022163340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311022164040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110221640423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110221640/original  a978-3-11-021952-4  E-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2009b2009  a978-3-11-023854-9  DGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  